# Node.js Authentication Backend Plan

We will create a Node.js backend using Express to handle user authentication (Sign Up and Log In). We'll use SQLite as a simple, file-based database so it requires no extra database server setup. 

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Infrastructure
We will create a new `backend` directory alongside the frontend folder.

#### [NEW] `backend/package.json`
Initialize a new Node.js project with `express`, `cors`, `bcrypt` (for password hashing), `jsonwebtoken` (for auth tokens), and `sqlite3`.

#### [NEW] `backend/server.js`
The main Express application entry point. It will configure middleware (CORS, JSON parsing) and mount the authentication routes.

#### [NEW] `backend/db.js`
Sets up the SQLite database connection and creates the `users` table if it doesn't exist.
- Table: `users` (id, name, email, password, role)

#### [NEW] `backend/routes/auth.js`
The authentication endpoints:
- `POST /api/auth/signup`: Accepts user details, hashes the password, and saves the user.
- `POST /api/auth/login`: Verifies user credentials and returns a JWT token.

